7
00:00:47,510 --> 00:00:49,770
 Nothing lasts forever. 

8
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:52,920
 There's nothing you can hold onto either. 

9
00:00:53,440 --> 00:00:58,650
 The only thing we can do is to live and love... 

10
00:00:59,260 --> 00:01:03,160
 today, at this moment. 

11
00:01:14,530 --> 00:01:18,510
Nice to meet you. I'm Ha Yeong Eun.

12
00:01:25,230 --> 00:01:29,220
I don't know what others might say,

13
00:01:29,220 --> 00:01:32,340
but Jae Gook is a very precious son to me.

14
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:37,360
He lived his entire life feeling small because of mistakes made by his elders.

15
00:01:37,970 --> 00:01:42,280
On top of that, once the whole world finds out whom he loves,

16
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:46,740
he'll have to live out the rest of his life the same way.

17
00:01:46,740 --> 00:01:53,440
So as his mother, I couldn't just sit idly by which is why I asked to meet you.

18
00:01:56,740 --> 00:02:00,620
How do you feel about Jae Gook?

19
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:06,110
Miss Ha Yeong Eun.

20
00:02:08,330 --> 00:02:11,850
How do you feel about him?

21
00:02:14,110 --> 00:02:16,080
It's love.

22
00:02:16,650 --> 00:02:21,250
I didn't give birth to him, but he's a brother to Soo Wan.

23
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:23,420
And I've already confirmed that

24
00:02:23,420 --> 00:02:28,470
my feelings won't change because of that fact.

25
00:02:29,220 --> 00:02:31,110
I see.

26
00:02:32,540 --> 00:02:34,790
Then please convince me.

27
00:02:34,790 --> 00:02:39,880
How certain you are, up to what point your sincerity lies...

28
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:43,310
If you can convince me,

29
00:02:43,820 --> 00:02:45,970
then I'll accept it.

30
00:02:51,890 --> 00:02:56,500
   

31
00:03:00,850 --> 00:03:04,430
   

32
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,300
   

33
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:10,940
Don't save it for Ji Min and eat it up!

34
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:15,590
Anyway, it looks like you passed one obstacle.

35
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,800
It was not what I expected.

36
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:22,240
But now there is a different concern about how I can convince her of my feelings.

37
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:24,950
As long as you two are happy, it's enough.

38
00:03:24,950 --> 00:03:27,800
There's no need to convince her.

39
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,680
Right?

40
00:03:32,330 --> 00:03:34,080
I'm laughing in front of you.

41
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:37,120
Hey, you have to laugh so I can, too.

42
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:39,960
"How's your illness? Is your condition all right?"

43
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:43,900
It's far better and more fun than the same old questions I've been getting.

44
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:47,520
Seeing you happy, hearing about it.

45
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:49,730
But what's all that?

46
00:03:50,620 --> 00:03:53,770
Hey, why am I losing so much weight?

47
00:03:53,770 --> 00:03:56,050
There is nothing I can wear.

48
00:03:56,050 --> 00:03:58,220
I am trying to organize ahead of time.

49
00:03:58,220 --> 00:03:59,890
Stop making me upset.

50
00:03:59,890 --> 00:04:01,220
Don't nag at me.

51
00:04:01,220 --> 00:04:04,640
As soon as my husband wakes up, he talks about chemo or getting hospitalized.

52
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:05,960
My ears are tired of his nagging.

53
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:08,920
Get chemo. Let's get you hospitalized.

54
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:11,830
After expecting and hoping...

55
00:04:11,830 --> 00:04:15,090
if the outcome is worse, then I will end up falling down even lower.

56
00:04:15,090 --> 00:04:20,100
Showing temper due to the pain, and then getting mad for others not being understanding...

57
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:22,920
I can't spend my time that way.

58
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:23,930
Mi Sook.

59
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:27,350
I want to say my goodbyes well.

60
00:04:28,180 --> 00:04:31,800
So I'm going to give my all to each day.

61
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:34,590
Until the last day that I am given,

62
00:04:34,590 --> 00:04:39,270
I am going to do everything I can so that I have no regrets...

63
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:42,260
I'm going to say my goodbyes well.

64
00:04:44,350 --> 00:04:46,820
I should throw these out before Ji Min comes home.

65
00:04:46,820 --> 00:04:50,130
She's seven, but there's a little lady living inside of her.

66
00:04:50,130 --> 00:04:53,180
Sometimes my answers aren't good enough.

67
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:55,880
Give them to me.

68
00:04:57,080 --> 00:05:00,960
It's cold these days. You can't catch a cold.

69
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:17,010
   

70
00:05:23,420 --> 00:05:26,440
You know why your friend is saying that.

71
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:29,770
But I can't acquiesce just like this and say goodbye.

72
00:05:29,770 --> 00:05:32,610
There are so many things I haven't done for Mi Sook.

73
00:05:32,610 --> 00:05:36,530
Like your friend said, do what you can today

74
00:05:36,530 --> 00:05:38,920
and then do what you can tomorrow.

75
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:41,780
Do everything you can for her.

76
00:05:42,290 --> 00:05:44,090
How's your mother?

77
00:05:44,090 --> 00:05:47,360
Has she said anything since?

78
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:51,510
Not yet. I don't really know what it means

79
00:05:51,510 --> 00:05:54,350
to convince her up to what point our sincerity lies,

80
00:05:54,350 --> 00:05:56,810
but let's just do what we've been doing.

81
00:05:56,810 --> 00:05:59,220
Let's do what we can.

82
00:06:01,170 --> 00:06:03,580
Oh, I'm here.

83
00:06:03,580 --> 00:06:05,240
Talk to you later.

84
00:06:27,350 --> 00:06:30,130
If it's for your girlfriend, these are nice.

85
00:06:30,130 --> 00:06:33,240
The meaning of pink roses is happy love.

86
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:35,430
Please make me a full bouquet then.

87
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:37,050
Okay.

88
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:42,930
This is why I told you I'd buy you an outfit for Dad's retirement ceremony.

89
00:06:42,930 --> 00:06:45,430
I'm going to stop living with your dad.

90
00:06:46,260 --> 00:06:48,590
Does this make you look older?

91
00:06:49,890 --> 00:06:54,120
Leave it! I can just put on whatever I get my hands on in the morning.

92
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,730
But you have to think about his reputation.

93
00:06:55,730 --> 00:06:58,890
Everyone will be coming by to say hello since you're the vice principal's wife.

94
00:06:58,890 --> 00:07:01,520
It's enough that for nearly 40 years I got up at 6 AM,

95
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:03,280
dunked my hands into cold water to cook and feed him breakfast,

96
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:04,960
and sent him on his way to work.

97
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,590
What more do I owe your dad?

98
00:07:07,590 --> 00:07:09,030
It's my graduation too.

99
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:11,930
On my graduation day, I want to dress however I want! What's wrong with that?!

100
00:07:11,930 --> 00:07:14,690
Then why did you call me over? You said it was urgent.

101
00:07:14,690 --> 00:07:17,660
It is urgent. Sit here.

102
00:07:19,790 --> 00:07:22,740
Get married before I get a divorce.

103
00:07:22,740 --> 00:07:24,990
Now you're threatening me?

104
00:07:24,990 --> 00:07:27,200
Let me live freely!

105
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:29,500
In two days, I'll be free of your dad!

106
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:33,210
Because of you, my life's homework isn't done!

107
00:07:33,210 --> 00:07:37,130
How long do I have to keep studying?

108
00:07:37,130 --> 00:07:38,990
- I have a man. 
 - Exactly!

109
00:07:38,990 --> 00:07:41,730
Huh? What?

110
00:07:41,730 --> 00:07:44,080
I have someone.

111
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:46,360
Oh, who is it? Who?

112
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:48,900
What does he do? How old is he?

113
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:54,320
When can I meet him? This girl!

114
00:07:56,420 --> 00:07:58,740
What's the occasion?

115
00:07:58,740 --> 00:08:00,740
To win some brownie points.

116
00:08:00,740 --> 00:08:03,020
I heard you met with Yeong Eun.

117
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:08,280
She told you to do this?

118
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:12,240
No. It was completely my idea.

119
00:08:13,150 --> 00:08:16,030
You must be hungry. What would you like me to make? What do you feel like eating?

120
00:08:16,030 --> 00:08:19,630
Spicy noodles. I came because I want to eat that, Mother.

121
00:08:19,630 --> 00:08:22,750
Okay, I understand. Wait here then.

122
00:08:41,230 --> 00:08:42,960
These pants only go up to size 66?

123
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,340
Yes, ma'am.

124
00:08:44,340 --> 00:08:47,800
But it comes oversized, so even sizes 66.5 can wear it.

125
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:48,940
I couldn't even zip it up.

126
00:08:48,940 --> 00:08:51,670
Excuse me, do you have one half size bigger?

127
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:55,870
Oh, we don't have half sizes.

128
00:08:57,140 --> 00:08:59,510
You're really not going to make more sizes?

129
00:08:59,510 --> 00:09:01,160
You know it's not that simple.

130
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:05,510
The Hills asked me to come work for their newly launched, imported brand instead of staying with Sonó.

131
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:07,800
So did you give them an answer?

132
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:09,520
I run my own business.

133
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:12,130
Handling old inventory monthly and paying my employees

134
00:09:12,130 --> 00:09:15,720
while selling domestic brands is not easy.

135
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:19,420
But I'm enduring it through waiting for the after effect of Galeries Lafayette.

136
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:24,600
It's not just me. Bigger store managers got offers too.

137
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,490
The world has become so diverse,

138
00:09:26,490 --> 00:09:29,520
but why do clothes still only come in three sizes: small, medium or large?

139
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:31,070
I'll make a strong proposal.

140
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:33,280
Don't make a proposal. Give me the result.

141
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,730
Who cares if the sales department keeps going on about

142
00:09:35,730 --> 00:09:37,820
how the sell-through percentage has to be over 60% to make a profit?

143
00:09:37,820 --> 00:09:40,720
You have to let us be able to sell. Don't you think?

144
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:43,040
Okay. I understand what you're saying.

145
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,980
So she wants to strike while the iron's hot.

146
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:47,930
I'm sure she's getting lots of customers with talk of Galeries Lafayette.

147
00:09:47,930 --> 00:09:49,460
Can you get me the report before the meeting?

148
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:51,390
 The chief is going to be screaming again. 

149
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:53,050
Probably.

150
00:09:55,570 --> 00:09:59,300
Yes, I'll be right there. Please take care of it until then.

151
00:10:24,550 --> 00:10:27,990
   

152
00:10:27,990 --> 00:10:31,060
There are sizes 44, 55, 66, and free size, too. 
  (Free size is a "one size fits all") 

153
00:10:31,060 --> 00:10:32,650
Why is she asking for more sizes?

154
00:10:32,650 --> 00:10:36,980
Sometimes sizes 77, 88 are the first ones to be sold out on home shopping networks.

155
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:38,540
That means there's a demand for them.

156
00:10:38,540 --> 00:10:39,920
Do different sizes appear out of thin air?

157
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:42,770
We need to make separate patterns and run different factories.

158
00:10:42,770 --> 00:10:45,380
That's all money! Money!

159
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:49,630
In the US, women's sizes go from 2, 4, 6 to 12.

160
00:10:49,630 --> 00:10:53,900
They differentiate long, regular, and short pants depending on leg length, too.

161
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:57,790
So customers are able to pick a size that fits them the best because there are many choices.

162
00:10:57,790 --> 00:11:00,190
That's because so many different races live in the US.

163
00:11:00,190 --> 00:11:03,560
At this rate, why don't you go visit each person and make them clothes to measure?!

164
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:06,290
I asked you to make something for Paris. What's this nonsense?

165
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:07,700
Stay true to your job!

166
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:10,390
Making clothes that suit the customers' needs

167
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:12,910
is also one of my jobs.

168
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:15,340
Hey, Team Leader Ha.

169
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:19,110
If we lose a competent store manager, we'll lose customers, too.

170
00:11:19,110 --> 00:11:22,420
Please consider it earnestly, Chief.

171
00:11:26,450 --> 00:11:31,150
We don't get along. We really don't get along!

172
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:33,800
Got over one hill...

173
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:36,300
Team Leader Ha! Yeong Eun!

174
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:39,420
Another hill to climb over is approaching me.

175
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:45,160
Has my father said anything?

176
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:47,340
Did you cause a problem? Why?

177
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:49,290
What is it? Who is it this time?

178
00:11:49,290 --> 00:11:51,730
What problem?

179
00:11:51,730 --> 00:11:54,890
Hey, CEO Seok confessed that he likes me.

180
00:11:56,130 --> 00:11:59,460
What's with that expression? I'm offended.

181
00:11:59,460 --> 00:12:02,640
Since when? Are you serious about him, too?

182
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:06,760
Hey, not me! You know he's not my type.

183
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:09,910
But how does CEO Hwang know about this?

184
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:13,880
Well... there was something...

185
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:16,410
Anyway, you're saying you did cause a problem.

186
00:12:16,410 --> 00:12:18,460
With the CEO of one of our subcontractors at that.

187
00:12:18,460 --> 00:12:22,830
Wench, you always think that you've got me figured out.

188
00:12:22,830 --> 00:12:26,650
But there is something I can do that you don't know about.

189
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:29,020
Where are you going in the middle of the conversation?

190
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:31,450
Don't you have to report to Father?

191
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:35,490
I'll go get the answer for you to write down.

192
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:05,000
 I know how foolish and reckless this emotion is.  

193
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:08,760
 But if I am this way regardless, it is because I am serious about Yoon Jae Gook.  

194
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:13,400
 But this self, this foolish and reckless self... I welcome it. 

195
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:19,910
 Why are you so reckless? Why are you so foolish? 

196
00:13:19,910 --> 00:13:22,270
 Even if we go through this marriage, we can't be happy. 

197
00:13:22,270 --> 00:13:25,150
 I thought I loved you but found out it's something else. 

198
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:29,140
 What we have is comfort from knowing each other for so long. Like a sibling or a friend. 

199
00:13:29,140 --> 00:13:32,210
 Our engagement period was too long, 

200
00:13:32,210 --> 00:13:35,510
 so you can think that. 

201
00:13:35,510 --> 00:13:37,420
 I'll try harder. 

202
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:40,460
 To me, you are still a man. 

203
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:44,010
 And I love you. 

204
00:13:44,010 --> 00:13:49,590
 With someone else in my heart, accepting you out of responsibility and duty... 

205
00:13:50,410 --> 00:13:53,040
 - That's not right. 
 - It doesn't matter. 

206
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:57,430
 It doesn't matter to me! So stay by my side. 

207
00:13:58,230 --> 00:14:00,150
 Don't go, Soo Wan. 

208
00:14:02,350 --> 00:14:04,330
   

209
00:14:14,170 --> 00:14:17,490
Soo Wan, you were the one who did me wrong.

210
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:21,330
She did me wrong.

211
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:02,010
I always watch the ending credits.

212
00:15:03,730 --> 00:15:08,070
Sometimes, those names that go up endlessly

213
00:15:08,070 --> 00:15:11,330
are more touching than the movie itself.

214
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:15,260
Because I can see

215
00:15:15,260 --> 00:15:20,400
how many people's time and effort went into this one movie.

216
00:15:21,780 --> 00:15:24,700
Missing the post-credit scene does feel quite terrible.

217
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:34,520
I like this music.

218
00:15:35,220 --> 00:15:40,060
♫  I'll give all I can to you  ♫

219
00:15:40,060 --> 00:15:45,700
♫  You'll always be the one I remember  ♫

220
00:15:46,530 --> 00:15:51,780
♫  You'll always take my breath away  ♫

221
00:15:51,780 --> 00:15:56,800
♫  You'll always be my heart, my life  ♫

222
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:59,590
♫  Every second, every day  ♫

223
00:15:59,590 --> 00:16:01,430
What should we go eat?

224
00:16:01,430 --> 00:16:04,570
Should we get Korean? Then what?

225
00:16:04,570 --> 00:16:08,420
- Today, I feel like— 
 - Are you... Jae Gook?

226
00:16:08,420 --> 00:16:12,350
Soo Wan's little brother, Yoon Jae Gook, right?

227
00:16:12,350 --> 00:16:16,540
- Hyung. 
 - Hey! How long has it been?

228
00:16:16,540 --> 00:16:20,230
You know Soo Wan, right? He's Soo Wan's brother.

229
00:16:22,110 --> 00:16:24,200
This is my wife.

230
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:26,140
Hello.

231
00:16:26,140 --> 00:16:28,200
It's hectic at the hospital,

232
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:31,980
but this kiddo wanted to watch an animated movie for her birthday present.

233
00:16:31,980 --> 00:16:33,750
Was it the anniversary of his death recently?

234
00:16:33,750 --> 00:16:36,130
Is that why you came back?

235
00:16:36,130 --> 00:16:37,680
Yes.

236
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:40,710
I'm too busy with life that I keep forgetting.

237
00:16:40,710 --> 00:16:44,830
- It's okay. 
 - By the way, you're resembling Soo Wan more and more.

238
00:16:44,830 --> 00:16:47,930
Like people won't know you're brothers, huh?

239
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,600
Who is she?

240
00:16:51,370 --> 00:16:54,410
This is my girlfriend.

241
00:16:54,410 --> 00:16:58,710
Oh, hello. I'm friend of Jae Gook's brother, Soo Wan.

242
00:16:58,710 --> 00:17:01,450
Hello, I'm Ha Yeong Eun.

243
00:17:08,510 --> 00:17:10,460
Goodbye.

244
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:17,620
Reality hit me straight in the face.

245
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:23,720
Hearing the name Soo Wan out of the blue nearly made my knees buckle.

246
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,340
Is that so?

247
00:17:25,340 --> 00:17:28,940
I think I lost about half of my fighting spirit too.

248
00:17:31,430 --> 00:17:34,050
You still have the other half left.

249
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:41,010
Why are there so many hills to climb over?

250
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:49,250
Since you're climbing anyway, let's go over one more hill.

251
00:17:52,060 --> 00:17:54,720
I want to meet

252
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:56,480
your mother too.

253
00:18:05,130 --> 00:18:06,760
What did you just say?

254
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:09,620
Help me out until the Paris deal is wrapped up.

255
00:18:09,620 --> 00:18:12,230
After it's all done, we say goodbye?

