00:45:25,960 --> 00:45:31,320
When sizes change and new patterns are created, we need to make at least 100 copies for training!

643
00:45:31,320 --> 00:45:35,760
To make one blouse, we draw it a hundred, a thousand times until we get it right.

644
00:45:35,760 --> 00:45:38,540
Then, we alter it. And after quality check, we make more alterations.

645
00:45:38,540 --> 00:45:41,560
To achieve this, we need three factories operating. Then what will happen to the other clothes in the meantime?

646
00:45:41,560 --> 00:45:43,660
And after all that, what if stock just piles up?

647
00:45:43,660 --> 00:45:45,390
Will you take all of the responsibility?

648
00:45:45,390 --> 00:45:49,530
How much longer will we hold on to an outdated sizing system from 40 years ago?

649
00:45:49,530 --> 00:45:52,120
Body types have changed, and the clothes that people want are changing.

650
00:45:52,120 --> 00:45:55,750
Despite that, people fit themselves well into the sizes and buy them just fine!

651
00:45:55,750 --> 00:45:57,990
Why does the body have to fit to the clothes?

652
00:45:57,990 --> 00:46:01,410
- The clothes should fit to the body. 
 - Really, will you keep talking back to me?

653
00:46:01,410 --> 00:46:06,700
Should I bring it up to the director or the CEO directly?

654
00:46:10,390 --> 00:46:14,560
Ah, seriously... seriously!

655
00:46:16,810 --> 00:46:19,320
I'm going to think about it for one more minute.

656
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:24,770
She's back.

657
00:46:27,570 --> 00:46:29,730
How did it go?

