00:47:15,600 --> 00:47:20,420
Now, I want to take pictures of people, not clothes.

671
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:23,720
  Let's take it together. 

672
00:47:26,490 --> 00:47:28,050
 I was always wandering around. 

673
00:47:28,050 --> 00:47:32,000
 Get closer. Closer. 

674
00:47:32,000 --> 00:47:34,810
 Because there was no place to settle my heart. 

675
00:47:34,810 --> 00:47:37,490
 Because there was no place to put it. 

676
00:47:44,640 --> 00:47:48,790
Being too close to, bumping into, and bothering each other.

677
00:47:48,790 --> 00:47:52,220
It felt nice. I wanted to keep doing it.

678
00:47:54,520 --> 00:47:58,160
To take pictures of people, you need to know who they are,

679
00:47:58,160 --> 00:48:03,020
what they're like, and what they like in order to express them.

680
00:48:03,650 --> 00:48:08,880
Are you two perhaps even thinking of marriage?

681
00:48:08,880 --> 00:48:11,400
If she wants to.

682
00:48:19,170 --> 00:48:22,870
Do you want to bring her home once?

683
00:48:25,500 --> 00:48:29,040
I want to make her a meal.

684
00:48:30,860 --> 00:48:32,540
Mother.

685
00:48:32,540 --> 00:48:34,450
Bring her home.

686
00:48:54,550 --> 00:48:56,230
What's all of this?

687
00:48:56,230 --> 00:48:58,330
You want to go back to your student life in Paris?

688
00:48:58,330 --> 00:49:03,190
It's been a while but I'm using the skills I had to practice twice because I had to do your homework too.

689
00:49:03,190 --> 00:49:07,140
It will take too long to complete by myself, so you can assist me this time.

690
00:49:07,140 --> 00:49:10,690
I'm already feeling so upset and sad from thinking about Mi Sook.

691
00:49:10,690 --> 00:49:13,600
I don't want to feel annoyance from assisting you on top of that.

692
00:49:13,600 --> 00:49:16,840
Whatever it is, work hard.

693
00:49:16,840 --> 00:49:18,980
These are clothes for Mi Sook.

694
00:49:23,420 --> 00:49:25,310
The clothes she bought with courage,

695
00:49:25,310 --> 00:49:27,400
the clothes she rashly bought when she was happy,

696
00:49:27,400 --> 00:49:29,550
the clothes she wore for the preschool event,

697
00:49:29,550 --> 00:49:33,510
and the clothes she wore to look cool on her wedding anniversary.

698
00:49:34,660 --> 00:49:37,050
These are all a part of her past,

699
00:49:37,050 --> 00:49:39,960
so I couldn't just leave them in the donation box.

700
00:49:40,770 --> 00:49:43,450
If they're too big, we can make them smaller.

701
00:49:43,450 --> 00:49:46,540
If they get bigger, we can re-make them even smaller.

702
00:49:48,510 --> 00:49:50,630
What should I do?

703
00:49:52,150 --> 00:49:54,910
We need to shorten the length, so cut the hem.

704
00:49:54,910 --> 00:49:57,580
I'm the best with scissors.

705
00:49:57,580 --> 00:49:59,960
- From here? 
 - Yeah.

706
00:50:15,450 --> 00:50:17,660
How is it? Do I look good?

707
00:50:17,660 --> 00:50:21,500
As expected, whoever the designer was that reformed it is amazing.

708
00:50:21,500 --> 00:50:24,360
Can you tell whoever it is that she wouldn't have been able to finish if it hadn't been for the assistant?

709
00:50:24,360 --> 00:50:27,260
Hey! I used to be a rising model years ago.

710
00:50:27,260 --> 00:50:28,840
Even though it was for a short time.

711
00:50:28,840 --> 00:50:31,640
Anyway, this skinny body

712
00:50:31,640 --> 00:50:34,800
is completing your work. What do you say?

713
00:50:34,800 --> 00:50:37,060
- You're right. 
 - 100%.

714
00:50:37,060 --> 00:50:38,460
It's so pretty.

715
00:50:38,460 --> 00:50:39,990
When did you wear this?

716
00:50:39,990 --> 00:50:42,480
For Ji Min's first birthday photo shoot.

717
00:50:42,480 --> 00:50:43,410
Oh, this is that?

718
00:50:43,410 --> 00:50:46,720
Try this on, too. This will complete the look.

719
00:50:46,720 --> 00:50:48,850
Wasn't this long before? Did you buy it?

720
00:50:48,850 --> 00:50:50,500
- No... Is this the long coat? 
 - Yeah.

721
00:50:50,500 --> 00:50:51,770
I cropped it.

722
00:50:51,770 --> 00:50:54,240
- She's acting like she did it all by herself again! 
 - It's a disease. A disease.

723
00:50:54,240 --> 00:50:56,510
I did the scissoring myself.

724
00:50:56,510 --> 00:50:58,310
Oh, you're all so skilled.

725
00:50:58,310 --> 00:50:59,680
It makes your legs look long. It's pretty.

726
00:50:59,680 --> 00:51:03,310
Yeah, I wanted to buy something like this. People wear it a lot these days.

727
00:51:03,310 --> 00:51:05,450
A cropped jacket like this.

728
00:51:12,300 --> 00:51:15,060
I think I'll get treatment.

729
00:51:15,060 --> 00:51:16,070
Mi Sook.

730
00:51:16,070 --> 00:51:17,510
Jeon Mi Sook!

731
00:51:17,510 --> 00:51:20,220
I was just thinking about throwing it away.

732
00:51:20,220 --> 00:51:23,360
I didn't know there were other methods.

733
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:26,740
If I want to say goodbye well,

734
00:51:26,740 --> 00:51:28,560
I need to live well first.

735
00:51:28,560 --> 00:51:30,060
I'm going to try till the end.

736
00:51:30,060 --> 00:51:31,770
"You did well."

737
00:51:31,770 --> 00:51:33,880
"You did all that you could."

738
00:51:33,880 --> 00:51:36,600
So I won't have any regrets.

739
00:51:36,600 --> 00:51:38,850
Thanks, Mi Sook.

740
00:51:38,850 --> 00:51:40,360
Thank you.

741
00:51:40,360 --> 00:51:41,680
Go to the VIP room.

742
00:51:41,680 --> 00:51:44,810
Yeah, let me use that money of yours.

743
00:51:46,000 --> 00:51:49,910
Hey, these clothes are calling for you to walk. Go walk!

744
00:51:49,910 --> 00:51:51,950
Show us your walk.

745
00:51:51,950 --> 00:51:54,250
Let's go with the power walk.

746
00:51:55,090 --> 00:51:56,780
Oh, your walk is still great.

747
00:51:56,780 --> 00:52:00,190
- Your talent didn't go anywhere! 
 - It's still great!

748
00:52:00,190 --> 00:52:01,470
Let's see.

749
00:52:01,470 --> 00:52:03,030
What is that?

750
00:52:03,030 --> 00:52:07,260
Hey, it's good that I lost weight! It makes these clothes look so good.

751
00:52:08,700 --> 00:52:11,940
Saying goodbye is also a method of love.

752
00:52:11,940 --> 00:52:15,980
It's been 20 years, since I was 18.

753
00:52:16,900 --> 00:52:20,420
I've spent half of my life with her.

754
00:52:21,100 --> 00:52:23,060
"Okay, yeah."

755
00:52:23,800 --> 00:52:25,860
"Goodbye."

756
00:52:26,600 --> 00:52:28,620
How can I do that?

757
00:52:28,620 --> 00:52:30,930
Does saying goodbye

758
00:52:30,930 --> 00:52:34,120
always have to be mushy and full of affection?

759
00:52:34,120 --> 00:52:37,660
That's just a stereotype.

760
00:52:38,700 --> 00:52:41,750
You should ease her heart before she passes.

761
00:52:41,750 --> 00:52:43,960
That's love, too.

762
00:52:51,500 --> 00:52:55,030
Love doesn't have just one side to it.

763
00:52:57,400 --> 00:53:00,490
Can I lean on you?

764
00:53:00,490 --> 00:53:02,800
Why do you even ask?

765
00:53:02,800 --> 00:53:05,720
My shoulder is yours whenever you need it.

766
00:53:05,720 --> 00:53:07,720
Whenever.

